The paper deals with game-theoretic models of voting behavior and proposes a new model that takes into account voters' bounded rationality and limited access to information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves simulations and convergence analysis, which are typical of the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with machine learning and decision-making, which are relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
